Think of the problem geometrically.  We can view $a,$ $b,$ $c,$ and $d$ as the side lengths of a quadrilateral.  Since the sum of the side lengths is 1, we can inscribe this quadrilateral in a unit circle.

[asy]
unitsize(2 cm);

pair A, B, C, D;

A = dir(110);
B = dir(210);
C = dir(330);
D = dir(0);

draw(Circle((0,0),1));
draw(A--B--C--D--cycle);

label("$a$", (A + B)/2, NW);
label("$b$", (B + C)/2, SW);
